  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Emergency Shelter Non-Food Items (NFI&apos;s) to Communities in Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Ethiopia, the internal displacement and humanitarian needs are mainly derived by the ongoing conflicts in different regions and floods in the country. The ongoing conflicts, climate shocks and displacements continue to pose serious protection concerns for the affected population. Most of the displaced population live in collective sites or in spontaneous settlements where they have limited access to essential services, dignified and safe living conditions and lack necessary resources to sustain their families and communities. Through this project, IOM is providing lifesaving humanitarian assistance focusing on emergency shelter, household, and hygiene items targeting internally displaced persons (IDPs), vulnerable returnees and vulnerable affected households from host communities.</narrative>
  </description>
